: 1.3px; text-align: inherit;"><br></span></p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; letter-spacing: 1.3px; text-align: inherit;">Think of collagen as the glue that holds your body together. Our bodies depend on collagen to keep our skin hydrated and plump, hair healthy, joints robust, muscles strong, and digestive system working properly.</span></p><p><br></p></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1606280258133" data-id="1606280258133"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" id="e-1606280649625" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1606280649625" data-resolution="1600x1600" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/63e09d6a-af69-425c-a9d9-e0a356f8a9f7/-/format/auto/-/preview/1600x1600/-/quality/lighter/" alt="" class="gf_image rte__no-indent" data-gemlang="en" data-width="90%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1073" natural-height="850"></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" class="gf_row" id="r-1606280548018" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1606280548018"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1606280547992" data-id="1606280547992"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606280724781" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606280724781"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 1.3px;"><br></b></p><p><b style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 1.3px;">How Collagen Affects Your Body with Age</b><br></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606280890519" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606280890519"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><br></p><p>Our bodies produce less collagen starting in our 20’s, at a decreasing rate of 1.5% <i>per year</i>. By our mid-late 40’s, our bodies loose up to 30% of our total collagen levels.&nbsp;</p><p><br></p><p>With this decline, our cells lose their structure and become weaker, thinner, and looser, leading to signs of aging, such as dry rough skin, wrinkles, brittle hair, hurting joints, and digestive issues.</p><p><br></p></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1606280548039" data-id="1606280548039"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" id="e-1606281064955" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1606281064955" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/3e1997ce-34e6-49b9-b5b8-0814f2475ca3/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="auto" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1080" natural-height="629"></div></div></div></div><!--gfsplit--><div data-label="Row" class="gf_row" id="r-1606326580472" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1606326580472"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1606326580484" data-id="1606326580484"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" id="e-1606326688176" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1606326688176" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: i